Results of the municipal by-elections held on 4 April 2018 During the by-elections contested yesterday in KwaZulu-Natal, the African National Congress (ANC) retained two seats and the Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP) gained one seat. The new councillors for the ANC are: Mbali Judith Cele in Ward 16 in the Umdoni Municipality – KZN212. The party retained the seat it won in the 2016 Municipal Elections, however with a reduced margin of 60.38% of the votes cast compared to 73.83% in the 2016 Municipal Elections. Voter turnout yesterday was 34.55%. Patience Nonhlanhla Maphanga in Ward 3 in the Mkhambathini Municipality – KZN226. The party retained the seat it won in the 2016 Municipal Elections, however with a slightly reduced margin of 54.63% of the votes cast compared to 56.24% in the 2016 Municipal Elections. Voter turnout yesterday was 38.94%. The new councillor for the IFP is Sibonelo Victor Mathenjwa in Ward 2 in Jozini Municipality – KZN272. The party won the seat from the ANC with 58.04% of the votes cast compared to 52.02% that the ANC received in the 2016 Municipal Elections. Voter turnout yesterday was 59.24%. For more detailed election results please visit the Electoral Commission’s website at www.elections.org.za. Statement issued by the Electoral Commission, 5 April 2018